data.enText: a creature with a shell, that lives in water, especially one of the types that can be eaten. Oysters and crabs are all shellfish .

tr: invertebrate having a soft unsegmented body usually enclosed in a shell
meat of edible aquatic invertebrate with a shell (especially a mollusk or crustacean)

value.def: Shellfish are small creatures that live in the sea and have a shell.

example.ex: Fish and shellfish are the specialities.
